  "texts": [
    "Consider any Z ∈ P such that x ∈ ■ i Z, so R i (x) ⊆ Z.",
    "If R i (x) ̸ ∈ Z, then by refinability for Z, there is a z ⊑ R i (x) such that for all z ′ ⊑ z, z ′ ̸ ∈ Z.",
    "Since z ⊑ R i (x), there is some y ∈ R i (x) such that z ∧ y ̸ = ⊥ (cf.",
    "Fact 5.12), so z ∧ y ⊑ y, but z ∧ y ̸ ∈ Z by the previous sentence.",
    "Then by persistence for Z, y ̸ ∈ Z, which contradicts the fact that y ∈ R i (x) ⊆ Z."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}